# Worldgen Breaking-Change Checklist

When editing or porting worldgen JSON, verify against this timeline. Prefer current APIs; do not reintroduce removed fields.

## 1.21.9–1.21.10

- [ ] `noise_router.preliminary_surface_level` exists (not `initial_density_without_jaggedness`)
- [ ] `pack.mcmeta` uses `min_format` / `max_format`

## 26.1

- [ ] No `flower` / `flower_no_bonemeal` / `random_patch` feature types
- [ ] Patches via placement modifiers; bone meal via `#can_spawn_from_bone_meal`
- [ ] `block_blob` / `spike` names; tree `below_trunk_provider`
- [ ] Dimension type: `has_ender_dragon_fight`, `default_clock` as needed

## 26.2 (pack 107.1)

- [ ] No `weird_scaled_sampler` — use `interval_select`
- [ ] No `noise_gradient` surface rule — use `noise_threshold` (+ optional `is_3d`)
- [ ] Speleothem renames + `base_block` / `pointed_block` / `replaceable_blocks`
- [ ] `lake` / `root_system` / `multiface_growth` required fields present
- [ ] `large_dripstone.column_radius` ≤ 16
- [ ] Structure processor chains account for sequential state evaluation
- [ ] No unknown/extra JSON keys (strict parse)

